Chewy Chai Spice Sugar Cookies
  --America's Test Kitchen
  
2 1/4 c (11 1/4 oz) unbleached ap flour
1/2 tsp baking soda
1 tsp baking powder
1/2 tsp salt
1/4 tsp cinnamon
1/4 tsp ground cardamom
1/4 tsp ground cloves
pinch ground black pepper
1 1/2 c (10 1/2 oz) sugar + 1/3 c for rolling
2 oz cream cheese, cut into 8 pieces
6 tbsp (3/4 stick) unsalted butter, melted and still warm
1/2 c vegetable oil
1 large egg
1 tbsp milk
1 tsp vanilla

Adjust oven rack to middle position and heat to 350F. Line 2 rimmed baking sheets with parchment paper. Whisk flour, baking soda, baking powder, and salt together in medium bowl; set aside. Place 1 1/2 c sugar, cream cheese, cinnamon, ginger, cardamom, cloves, and black peppre in large bowl. Place remaining 1/3 c sugar in shallow baking dish or pie tin and set aside. Pour warm butter over sugar mixture and whisk to combine, some small lumps of cream cheese may remain, but will smooth out later. Whisk in oil until incorporated. Add egg, milk, and vanilla; continue to whisk until smooth. Add flour mixture and mix with rubber spatula until soft homogeneous dough forms. Divide dough into 24 equal pieces, ~2 tbsp each (#40 portion scoop). Using hands, roll dough into balls. Working in batches, roll balls in reserved sugar to coat and evenly space on prepared baking sheet, 12 per sheet. Using bottom of drinking glass, flatten dough balls until 2" in diameter. Sprinkle tops evenly with 4 tsp of sugar (remaining in shallow dish), discarding any remaining sugar. Bake 1 tray at a time, until edges are set and just beginning to brown, 11-13 min, rotating tray after 7 min. cool cookies on baking sheets 5 min before removing to wire rack to cool to room temp.


Notes: For best results, handle dough as little as possible,
